messages.content:
The user wants to know if the fireplace lights device is currently on or off. This requires checking the COS of the "Status" property of the device "fireplace lights". The "Status" property is an enum with values Off [0] and On [100]. We will create a condition that checks if the "Status" is On (100) or Off (0) and return the status accordingly.

Since the user query is a status inquiry, the automation routine will be a condition check without an action, effectively a query routine that can be used to report the current state.

The routine will be named "Check Fireplace Lights Status" and will include a condition that checks the "Status" property of "fireplace lights". The output is structured as a JSONLogic condition that can be used to determine the device state.

{
  "automation": {
    "name": "Check Fireplace Lights Status",
    "condition": {
      "or": [
        {
          "==": {
            "device": "fireplace lights",
            "status": "Status",
            "value": 100,
            "uom": "percent",
            "precision": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "==": {
            "device": "fireplace lights",
            "status": "Status",
            "value": 0,
            "uom": "percent",
            "precision": 0
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
